commits.message:
The parsing for the SWF url was wrong (the "//" are now escaped and the initial .*match needs to be 'ungreedy'), so the -W setting to rtmpdump was not set, causing the decryption of the video to be wrong.

Also only setting "-q" to rtmpdump if "-q" is sent to youtube-dl

Finally, add "&has_verified=1" to the fetch of the HMTL page to allow fetching of age-restricted videos

commits.message:
Fix WAF OR statement bug and add rate limiting support

  - Fix issue with OR statement requiring minimum 2 child statements
    by using conditional logic to avoid OR when only one IP set exists
  - Add rate limiting support with configurable parameters:
    - enable_rate_limiting: Enable/disable rate limiting
    - rate_limit_requests: Number of requests allowed per IP
    - rate_limit_evaluation_window_sec: Time window in seconds

  This fixes deployment errors when using only IPv4 or IPv6 allowlists
  and enables per-IP rate limiting for CloudFront distributions
commits.author: Wayne Workman
